reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good enough to buy twice.
reviews.reviewText: I bought a pack of these almost a year ago and they've really held up. They haven't worn out, lost their color, or shrunk. They're soft cotton (I don't like to wear synthetic underwear) and look nice. They also cover just about my entire (very large) bum. There are some that cover more, but none that look as nice. These I can wear on date night.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic comfortable and cute undies
reviews.reviewText: This is my second purchase of these underwear in the past year. I am replacing all of my other undies because these are just so cute, comfortable and affordable. You can’t go wrong with these!I am 5’5” and about 127lbs and I bought the medium sized pack and have not had them shrink at all that I can tell.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not sexy, but very functional!
reviews.reviewText: True to size and look and feel very practical. They are flattering, comfortable, and just seem like they will be very dependable cotton panties. They don’t squeeze my hips or cause a bump and the lace is a nice touch. I got size Medium and that’s the size I usually wear in pantries and leggings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice cotton panty but does shrink for skinny folks! Belly beware!
reviews.reviewText: I find it hard to find cute & comfy panties that don’t make me feel like I borrowed from my grandma. I am 5’5” and weigh 166 pounds. It is tough to find a panty that sits comfortably right beneath the belly button without being too tight or too loose. Especially without extenuating my belly. The mid rise or modern brief or high rise hipster is as close as I have found. These are slightly low rise for my comfort as they felt like they were slipping constantly. The fabric is super soft and lace trim flattering and stretched nicely. Even, after tugging a bit at them on day two I have not had any tears from the seams. They shrunk terribly even after I washed on cold and dried on low. What a shame. I would recommend buying a size up if you intend on machine drying them. Also, I really do not recommend if you have even the slightest belly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very comfy, small fits perfect with someone who has a small waist. Cute colors

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: So I was excited to wear these as the material felt so soft in my hand and the first pair I wore felt heavenly comfortable. I went on treadmill with them on and when I went to shower afterward found a HUGE tear in the right side to the right bun. Unbelievable! I’m super disappointed and concerned the others could tear from what exactly? Was it there when I put them on but did not notice? Now I have to return them - what a drag, I wanted to love them they are sporty/sexy and I’m going to give them a pass on the rip unless it happens again than I’ll have to give 2 stars. If they are good to go after a few months I’ll up it to 4 stars.
